    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small openings, often obliquely cut, in the wall of a church, generally so placed as to afford a view of the high altar from the transept or aisles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
